ssibility of a realignment of British politics. This study will be invaluable to anyone interested in the turbulent and transitional nature of British politics during a watershed period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCabinet officerszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aPoliticianszGreat BritainvBiography. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aLabour Government.  aLabour Right.  aPrentice.  arealignment.  asocial democracy.1 aHorn, Geoff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611083140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526110831423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526110831/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles